HEADWORD: Hazarder
<hw>Haz"ard*er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A player at the game of hazard; a gamester.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who hazards or ventures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hazardize</ent>⟦br⟧
